  "chunk_index": 19,
  "summary": "During a discussion regarding the murder of Prince Michael, Chief Balthazar and other guests dismiss the Red Hand Brotherhood as suspects. Balthazar suggests the investigation suffers from a \"mental blind spot\" concerning Hessian royalists and the potential for a new king. Roxanne reveals that Prince Nikolai, Michael's cousin, is the likely heir. Roemex describes Nikolai as an eccentric former Oxford student who has recently reappeared in America. Balthazar and Isakov explain that while monarchists support Michael, Nikolai’s democratic views could make him a puppet for an American consortium seeking oil concessions.\n\nGeorge questions why Captain Androidsi did not accompany the Prince. Balthazar explains that the Captain remained in the city to arrange a secret date for Michael. The conversation then shifts to Victor King, an infamous French con artist and jewel thief believed to be in Britain. Balthazar hypothesizes that King may have come to Chimney House to find the \"Diamond of Light Mountain\" (referred to as \"K\") and accidentally killed the Prince, though he notes King has no history of murder.\n\nThe group decides to interview the Prince's servants and summons Boris Anchukov, Michael's personal servant. Upon hearing of the murder, Anchukov reacts with a wild howl, expressing intense grief and self-reproach for potentially being drugged and failing his master. He declares a fierce desire for vengeance, brandishing a large knife and describing a violent plan to mutilate and kill the murderer.",
